{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "What technical problems may one encounter when trying to use a classifier found online?",
    "One problem is that the data provided by the eye tracker does not match the expected input format for the classifier.",
    "In this case, a data input function has to be written to solve issues such as ensuring that timestamps have the right unit, that gaze data columns have the expected names and that gaze data are converted to degrees (see the section \"Converting pixels and millimeters to degrees\") if the classifier requires that but the gaze data provided by the eye tracker is expressed in pixels on a computer screen.",
    "Another consideration might be how to evaluate the performance of event classification algorithms.",
    "Startsev and Zemblys (2023) provides a discussion of this problem."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Startsev and Zemblys (2023) provides a discussion of this problem."
  ]
}